* {{ill|Shiki Mikenoza Shrine|ja|志貴御県坐神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Sakurai City, Miwa Kanaya)
* {{ill|Tōchi Mikenoza Shrine|ja|十市御縣坐神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Kashihara City, Tōchi)
* {{ill|Takechi Mikenoza Shrine|ja|高市御県神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Kashihara City, Shijō)
* {{ill|Katsuragi Mikenoza Shrine|ja|葛木御県神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Katsuragi City, Katsuragi)

Among the 27 prayers listed in the ''{{ill|Engishiki|ja|延喜式|qq=draft|qq=draft}}'', the {{ill|Kinensai|ja|祈年祭|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Harvest Prayer Festival) specifically mentions offerings from these six counties, primarily vegetables. The six counties occupied the entirety of the {{ill|Nara Basin|ja|奈良盆地|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, but their extent was not vast.

In {{ill|624|ja|624th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (32nd year of {{ill|Empress Suiko|ja|推古天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft}}), {{ill|Soga no Umako|ja|蘇我馬子|qq=draft|qq=draft}} petitioned Empress Suiko to grant him Katsuragi County as a private estate, citing it as the ancestral homeland of the Soga clan and the origin of their noble title ("Omi"). However, the empress, despite being of Soga descent, rejected the request.<ref>''Nihon Shoki'', Volume 22, entry on Empress Suiko, 32nd Year, 10th Month.</ref>

