* '''Sofu (Soe) County''' (曽布・添県) - [[:en:Soekami District, Nara|Soegami District]], {{ill|Soeshimo District|ja|添下郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Soeshimo District|qq=}} * '''Yamanobe County''' (山辺県) - [[:en:Yamabe District, Nara|Yamanobe District]] * '''Shiki County''' (磯城県) - {{ill|Shikijō District|ja|式上郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikijō District|qq=}}, {{ill|Shikige District|ja|式下郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikige District|qq=}} * '''Tōchi County''' (十市県) - {{ill|Tōchi District|ja|十市郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tōchi District|qq=}} * '''Takechi County''' (高市県) - [[:en:Takaichi District, Nara|Takechi District]] * '''Katsuragi County''' (葛城県) - {{ill|Katsujō District|ja|葛上郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katsujō District|qq=}}, {{ill|Katsuge District|ja|葛下郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katsuge District|qq=}}
Within these areas, several shrines bearing the name of their respective counties were established as {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|qq=}}, including: * {{ill|Soe Mikenoza Shrine|ja|添御県坐神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Soe Mikenoza Shrine|qq=}} (Nara City, Miutsuka and Utahime) * {{ill|Yamanobe Mikenoza Shrine|ja|山邊御県坐神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamanobe Mikenoza Shrine|qq=}} (Tenri City, Bessho and Nishiidodō) * {{ill|Shiki Mikenoza Shrine|ja|志貴御県坐神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shiki Mikenoza Shrine|qq=}} (Sakurai City, Miwa Kanaya) * {{ill|Tōchi Mikenoza Shrine|ja|十市御縣坐神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tōchi Mikenoza Shrine|qq=}} (Kashihara City, Tōchi) * {{ill|Takechi Mikenoza Shrine|ja|高市御県神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takechi Mikenoza Shrine|qq=}} (Kashihara City, Shijō) * {{ill|Katsuragi Mikenoza Shrine|ja|葛木御県神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katsuragi Mikenoza Shrine|qq=}} (Katsuragi City, Katsuragi)
Among the 27 prayers listed in the ''[[:en:Engishiki|Engishiki]]'', the [[:en:Kinen-sai|Kinensai]] (Harvest Prayer Festival) specifically mentions offerings from these six counties, primarily vegetables. The six counties occupied the entirety of the [[:en:Nara Basin|Nara Basin]], but their extent was not vast.
In [[:en:624|624]] (32nd year of [[:en:Empress Suiko|Empress Suiko]]), [[:en:Soga no Umako|Soga no Umako]] petitioned Empress Suiko to grant him Katsuragi County as a private estate, citing it as the ancestral homeland of the Soga clan and the origin of their noble title ("Omi"). However, the empress, despite being of Soga descent, rejected the request.<ref>''Nihon Shoki'', Volume 22, entry on Empress Suiko, 32nd Year, 10th Month.</ref>
